lta":17,"uuid":"7ced15ef-9c7b-4afc-95f5-40df6fc0d7d1","session_id":"09d2d379-4cbc-4745-9b7a-9acf62397c86"},{"type":"system","subtype":"thinking_tokens","estimated_tokens":1588,"estimated_tokens_delta":2,"uuid":"4f9a6a50-a844-45b3-8e54-656c1f19bc61","session_id":"09d2d379-4cbc-4745-9b7a-9acf62397c86"},{"type":"system","subtype":"thinking_tokens","estimated_tokens":1590,"estimated_tokens_delta":2,"uuid":"b2533fb4-f118-480d-b414-5c2d9d3fa8df","session_id":"09d2d379-4cbc-4745-9b7a-9acf62397c86"},{"type":"system","subtype":"thinking_tokens","estimated_tokens":1611,"estimated_tokens_delta":21,"uuid":"91625444-d3db-4a35-befb-8554e24c6892","session_id":"09d2d379-4cbc-4745-9b7a-9acf62397c86"},{"type":"system","subtype":"thinking_tokens","estimated_tokens":1613,"estimated_tokens_delta":2,"uuid":"9392d29c-3419-4035-aed3-7a573f85a496","session_id":"09d2d379-4cbc-4745-9b7a-9acf62397c86"},{"type":"system","subtype":"thinking_tokens","estimated_tokens":5015,"estimated_tokens_delta":3402,"uuid":"63b86b6a-9896-4b38-a026-c5582aafc7e2","session_id":"09d2d379-4cbc-4745-9b7a-9acf62397c86"},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01GLCYS77rJoxvs6KE1G8urF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. Let me plan the implementation:\n\n1. **`word_garden/ui.py`** — pure rendering, no I/O:\n   - `render(state, ascii_mode=False) -> str`: full turn display\n   - `win_screen(state, ascii_mode=False) -> str`\n   - `loss_screen(state, ascii_mode=False) -> str`\n   - Growth stages based on progress\n   - Emoji mode vs ASCII mode\n\n2. **`word_garden/main.py`** — the only I/O module:\n   - `main(argv=None, input_fn=input, output_fn=print) -> int`\n   - Command-line argument parsing for difficulty and ASCII mode\n   - Main game loop with EOF and interrupt handling\n\n3. **`word_garden/__main__.py`** — entry point\n\n4. **`tests/test_ui.py`** — tests for UI\n\n5. **`README.md`** — project docs\n\nFor the UI, I'm mapping out the plant growth stages: seedling at the start, growing leaves as progress increases, flowering when near victory, full bloom on win, and wilting on loss.\n\nFor ASCII mode, I need fallback characters like `*`, `+`, `@`, `$`, and `x` since emojis won't work.\n\nThe progress calculation should track what proportion of the word's unique letters have been revealed. I'm thinking: 0 letters revealed is the start, any letters guessed moves to progress, 60% or more of unique letters revealed signals near-win, then the actual win and loss states.\n\nNow I'm looking at the render structure from the spec—it should display the game title, current plant status, the hidden word with revealed letters, guessed letters so far, remaining water count, weed count, and a prompt for the next guess. Water and weeds need text labels with counts, never symbols alone. I'm sketching out the exact display format with both emoji and ASCII modes—using symbols like `*`, `+`, `@`, `$`, `x` for the different growth stages in ASCII mode to keep it readable.\n\nFor the win and loss screens, I'm defining the emoji versions with a blooming flower for victory and a wilted one for defeat, then creating ASCII equivalents that convey the same outcome. Now I'm implementing the UI module with growth stage thresholds and display logic. Defining the growth stage logic... Building the display output... Writing the main game loop... I see the issue now—when invalid input is detected, I should show the error message and re-prompt without re-rendering the full game state, since that would consume a turn. The loop needs to distinguish between validation failures (which loop back to the prompt) and successful guesses (which loop back to the render). I'm restructuring the input validation to use an inner loop that keeps re-prompting for invalid input without re-rendering the board, which matches the spec better. The outer loop renders the board once per turn, then the inner loop handles getting a valid letter guess with error messages shown inline. I'm also realizing that the prompt text needs to appear on the same line as the cursor, which is tricky with separate print calls. the prompt gets passed to the fake input function and ignored in tests. For the end game flow, after the main loop exits, I display either a win or loss screen through output_fn depending on the game state. This keeps the structure clean and straightforward.\n\nNow I'm looking at the actual win and loss screen examples from the spec to make sure they match what I've defined. They look correct. The question is whether I should show the final board state before displaying the end screen, or just show the end screen directly. The spec describes the loop as rendering state, prompting for input, validating, and applying guesses until game over, but it's not entirely clear if the final board state should appear before the win/loss message.\n\nLooking at my current loop structure, the board gets rendered at the top of each iteration, so the last board shown is actually from before the final guess. Once the game ends, I skip rendering and go straight to the win/loss screen. The spec says to show the win/loss screen and return, but I'm still uncertain whether the final board state should be displayed first.\n\nI'm noticing there's a difference between the status messages in game.py and the formatted win/loss screens in ui.py. The game.py messages are simpler templates, while the ui.py screens have additional formatting and emoji. I need to figure out which ones to use for the final output.\n\nNow I'm thinking about how to handle the goodbye message when the user exits via EOF or KeyboardInterrupt. The spec requires a friendly goodbye and a clean exit with code 0. I should wrap the exception handling around the game loop to catch input errors, though I need to be careful about where exactly to place it so it doesn't interfere with normal output.\n\nFor the goodbye message itself, I'm considering whether to use a newline prefix to clear the input prompt line if the interrupt happens while waiting for input. Using `output_fn` with a newline prefix handles both regular print and test scenarios where `output_fn` might be a different function like list appending.\n\nNow I'm thinking through what tests I need to write for the UI module - covering the render function in both emoji and ASCII modes, all the growth stages, win and loss screens in both modes, and end-to-end tests for winning and losing scenarios. For those integration tests, I'll need to mock the input and output functions.\n\nThe key constraint from the spec is that any test touching randomness must inject a seeded random instance rather than relying on global state. For the unit tests of individual rendering functions, I can construct a GameState object directly with fixed values instead of calling the randomized constructor.\n\nFor the end-to-end test of `main()`, I need to control which word gets selected. Since `main()` doesn't expose the RNG parameter, I'll use `unittest.mock.patch` to monkeypatch `new_game` to return a GameState with a known word, which is cleaner than trying to modify `main()` itself.\n\nFor the win test, I'll set up a state with secret_word = \"CAT\" and feed in those letters as inputs to verify the game ends in victory. For the loss test, I'll use the same word but limit max_water to 2, then provide wrong guesses like \"Z\" and \"X\" to exhaust the water and trigger a loss.\n\nLet me check what the existing test files look like to match the testing style they're using.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":184,"cache_read_input_tokens":34159,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":184},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09d2d379-4cbc-4745-9b7a-9acf62397c86","uuid":"4e38445b-2682-482e-8b51-37bd26e98c14","request_id":"req_011CbxgFnpBMTA5yKbvQE4yx"},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01GLCYS77rJoxvs6KE1G8urF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Let me quickly check the existing tests for style reference:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":184,"cache_read_input_tokens":34159,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":184},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09d2d379-4cbc-4745-9b7a-9acf62397c86","uuid":"9e8e0da8-da6a-4d23-b9c8-a253727a4d88","request_id":"req_011CbxgFnpBMTA5yKbvQE4yx"},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01GLCYS77rJoxvs6KE1G8urF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_014vdYH992vRYYCJV9a1DPwj","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/task-002-w3/tests/test_game.py"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":184,"cache_read_input_tokens":34159,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":184},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09d2d379-4cbc-4745-9b7a-9acf62397c86","uuid":"ce153094-05f9-4a9a-8e17-add5acfd47be","request_id":"req_011CbxgFnpBMTA5yKbvQE4yx"},{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014vdYH992vRYYCJV9a1DPwj","type":"tool_result","content":"1\timport random\n2\timport unittest\n3\t\n4\tfrom word_garden.game import (\n5\t    GameState,\n6\t    apply_guess,\n7\t    display_word,\n8\t    is_lost,\n9\t    is_won,\n10\t    new_game,\n11\t    validate_guess,\n12\t    MSG_ALREADY_GUESSED_TEMPLATE,\n13\t    MSG_CORRECT,\n14\t    MSG_GAME_OVER,\n15\t    MSG_INCORRECT,\n16\t    MSG_INVALID_NOT_LETTER,\n17\t    MSG_INVALID_NOT_SINGLE,\n18\t    MSG_LOSS_TEMPLATE,\n19\t    MSG_WIN_TEMPLATE,\n20\t)\n21\t\n22\t\n23\tdef _make_state(**kwargs) -> GameState:\n24\t    \"\"\"Build a GameState with sensible defaults, overridden by kwargs.\"\"\"\n25\t    defaults = dict(\n26\t        secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n27\t        guessed_letters=set(),\n28\t        remaining_water=6,\n29\t        weed_count=0,\n30\t        max_water=6,\n31\t    )\n32\t    defaults.update(kwargs)\n33\t    return GameState(**defaults)\n34\t\n35\t\n36\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n37\t# new_game\n38\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n39\t\n40\tclass TestNewGame(unittest.TestCase):\n41\t    def test_initial_state_fields(self):\n42\t        rng = random.Random(42)\n43\t        state = new_game(\"normal\", rng=rng)\n44\t        self.assertIsInstance(state.secret_word, str)\n45\t        self.assertTrue(state.secret_word.isupper())\n46\t        self.assertEqual(state.guessed_letters, set())\n47\t        self.assertEqual(state.remaining_water, 6)\n48\t        self.assertEqual(state.max_water, 6)\n49\t        self.assertEqual(state.weed_count, 0)\n50\t        self.assertEqual(state.status_message, \"\")\n51\t        self.assertFalse(state.game_over)\n52\t        self.assertFalse(state.won)\n53\t\n54\t    def test_easy_water_level(self):\n55\t        state = new_game(\"easy\", rng=random.Random(1))\n56\t        self.assertEqual(state.remaining_water, 8)\n57\t        self.assertEqual(state.max_water, 8)\n58\t\n59\t    def test_hard_water_level(self):\n60\t        state = new_game(\"hard\", rng=random.Random(1))\n61\t        self.assertEqual(state.remaining_water, 4)\n62\t        self.assertEqual(state.max_water, 4)\n63\t\n64\t\n65\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n66\t# validate_guess — Test 5 (invalid input) and Test 6 (lowercase normalised)\n67\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n68\t\n69\tclass TestValidateGuess(unittest.TestCase):\n70\t    # Test 5: Invalid input is rejected with a specific message.\n71\t\n72\t    def test_empty_string_rejected(self):\n73\t        letter, msg = validate_guess(\"\")\n74\t        self.assertIsNone(letter)\n75\t        self.assertEqual(msg, MSG_INVALID_NOT_SINGLE)\n76\t\n77\t    def test_whitespace_only_rejected(self):\n78\t        letter, msg = validate_guess(\"   \")\n79\t        self.assertIsNone(letter)\n80\t        self.assertEqual(msg, MSG_INVALID_NOT_SINGLE)\n81\t\n82\t    def test_multiple_letters_rejected(self):\n83\t        letter, msg = validate_guess(\"AB\")\n84\t        self.assertIsNone(letter)\n85\t        self.assertEqual(msg, MSG_INVALID_NOT_SINGLE)\n86\t\n87\t    def test_word_rejected(self):\n88\t        letter, msg = validate_guess(\"apple\")\n89\t        self.assertIsNone(letter)\n90\t        self.assertEqual(msg, MSG_INVALID_NOT_SINGLE)\n91\t\n92\t    def test_digit_rejected(self):\n93\t        letter, msg = validate_guess(\"7\")\n94\t        self.assertIsNone(letter)\n95\t        self.assertEqual(msg, MSG_INVALID_NOT_LETTER)\n96\t\n97\t    def test_symbol_rejected(self):\n98\t        letter, msg = validate_guess(\"!\")\n99\t        self.assertIsNone(letter)\n100\t        self.assertEqual(msg, MSG_INVALID_NOT_LETTER)\n101\t\n102\t    # Test 6: Lowercase input is normalised to uppercase.\n103\t\n104\t    def test_lowercase_normalised(self):\n105\t        letter, msg = validate_guess(\"a\")\n106\t        self.assertEqual(letter, \"A\")\n107\t        self.assertEqual(msg, \"\")\n108\t\n109\t    def test_leading_trailing_spaces_stripped(self):\n110\t        letter, msg = validate_guess(\"  b  \")\n111\t        self.assertEqual(letter, \"B\")\n112\t        self.assertEqual(msg, \"\")\n113\t\n114\t    def test_valid_uppercase_accepted(self):\n115\t        letter, msg = validate_guess(\"Z\")\n116\t        self.assertEqual(letter, \"Z\")\n117\t        self.assertEqual(msg, \"\")\n118\t\n119\t\n120\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n121\t# apply_guess — Tests 1–4, 7–8\n122\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n123\t\n124\tclass TestApplyGuessCorrect(unittest.TestCase):\n125\t    # Test 1: A correct guess reveals matching letters.\n126\t\n127\t    def test_correct_guess_adds_letter_to_guessed(self):\n128\t        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\")\n129\t        result = apply_guess(state, \"G\")\n130\t        self.assertIn(\"G\", result.guessed_letters)\n131\t        self.assertEqual(result.remaining_water, 6)\n132\t        self.assertEqual(result.weed_count, 0)\n133\t        self.assertEqual(result.status_message, MSG_CORRECT)\n134\t        self.assertFalse(result.game_over)\n135\t        self.assertFalse(result.won)\n136\t\n137\t    def test_correct_guess_display_reveals_letter(self):\n138\t        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\")\n139\t        result = apply_guess(state, \"G\")\n140\t        # GARDEN with only G revealed → G _ _ _ _ _\n141\t        self.assertEqual(display_word(result), \"G _ _ _ _ _\")\n142\t\n143\t    def test_correct_guess_recurring_letter_all_positions_revealed(self):\n144\t        # SEEDLING has two E's; both should appear in display\n145\t        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"SEEDLING\")\n146\t        result = apply_guess(state, \"E\")\n147\t        self.assertIn(\"E\", result.guessed_letters)\n148\t        displayed = display_word(result)\n149\t        parts = displayed.split(\" \")\n150\t        self.assertEqual(parts[1], \"E\")  # index 1 in SEEDLING\n151\t        self.assertEqual(parts[2], \"E\")  # index 2 in SEEDLING\n152\t\n153\t\n154\tclass TestApplyGuessIncorrect(unittest.TestCase):\n155\t    # Tests 2 & 3: An incorrect guess reduces water by one and adds one weed.\n156\t\n157\t    def test_incorrect_guess_water_weed_letter(self):\n158\t        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\")\n159\t        result = apply_guess(state, \"Z\")\n160\t        self.assertIn(\"Z\", result.guessed_letters)\n161\t        self.assertEqual(result.remaining_water, 5)\n162\t        self.assertEqual(result.weed_count, 1)\n163\t        self.assertEqual(result.status_message, MSG_INCORRECT)\n164\t        self.assertFalse(result.game_over)\n165\t        self.assertFalse(result.won)\n166\t\n167\t    def test_incorrect_guess_exact_decrements(self):\n168\t        state = _make_state(remaining_water=4, weed_count=2)\n169\t        result = apply_guess(state, \"Z\")\n170\t        self.assertEqual(result.remaining_water, 3)\n171\t        self.assertEqual(result.weed_count, 3)\n172\t\n173\t\n174\tclass TestApplyGuessRepeated(unittest.TestCase):\n175\t    # Test 4: Repeated guesses do not reduce water or weeds.\n176\t\n177\t    def test_repeated_correct_letter_no_change(self):\n178\t        state = _make_state(\n179\t            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n180\t            guessed_letters={\"G\"},\n181\t            remaining_water=6,\n182\t            weed_count=0,\n183\t        )\n184\t        result = apply_guess(state, \"G\")\n185\t        self.assertEqual(result.remaining_water, 6)\n186\t        self.assertEqual(result.weed_count, 0)\n187\t        self.assertEqual(result.guessed_letters, {\"G\"})\n188\t        self.assertEqual(\n189\t            result.status_message,\n190\t            MSG_ALREADY_GUESSED_TEMPLATE.format(letter=\"G\"),\n191\t        )\n192\t        self.assertFalse(result.game_over)\n193\t        self.assertFalse(result.won)\n194\t\n195\t    def test_repeated_wrong_letter_no_change(self):\n196\t        state = _make_state(\n197\t            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n198\t            guessed_letters={\"Z\"},\n199\t            remaining_water=5,\n200\t            weed_count=1,\n201\t        )\n202\t        result = apply_guess(state, \"Z\")\n203\t        self.assertEqual(result.remaining_water, 5)\n204\t        self.assertEqual(result.weed_count, 1)\n205\t        self.assertEqual(result.guessed_letters, {\"Z\"})\n206\t        self.assertEqual(\n207\t            result.status_message,\n208\t            MSG_ALREADY_GUESSED_TEMPLATE.format(letter=\"Z\"),\n209\t        )\n210\t\n211\t\n212\tclass TestApplyGuessWin(unittest.TestCase):\n213\t    # Test 7: The game detects a win.\n214\t\n215\t    def test_win_on_last_letter(self):\n216\t        state = _make_state(\n217\t            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n218\t            guessed_letters={\"G\", \"A\", \"R\", \"D\", \"E\"},\n219\t            remaining_water=6,\n220\t            weed_count=0,\n221\t        )\n222\t        result = apply_guess(state, \"N\")\n223\t        self.assertIn(\"N\", result.guessed_letters)\n224\t        self.assertTrue(result.game_over)\n225\t        self.assertTrue(result.won)\n226\t        self.assertEqual(result.remaining_water, 6)\n227\t        self.assertEqual(result.weed_count, 0)\n228\t        self.assertEqual(result.status_message, MSG_WIN_TEMPLATE.format(word=\"GARDEN\"))\n229\t        self.assertTrue(is_won(result))\n230\t        self.assertFalse(is_lost(result))\n231\t\n232\t    def test_guess_after_win_is_noop(self):\n233\t        state = _make_state(game_over=True, won=True, remaining_water=6, weed_count=0)\n234\t        result = apply_guess(state, \"X\")\n235\t        self.assertEqual(result.remaining_water, 6)\n236\t        self.assertEqual(result.weed_count, 0)\n237\t        self.assertTrue(result.game_over)\n238\t        self.assertTrue(result.won)\n239\t        self.assertEqual(result.status_message, MSG_GAME_OVER)\n240\t\n241\t\n242\tclass TestApplyGuessLoss(unittest.TestCase):\n243\t    # Test 8: The game detects a loss.\n244\t\n245\t    def test_loss_on_final_water(self):\n246\t        state = _make_state(\n247\t            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n248\t            remaining_water=1,\n249\t            weed_count=5,\n250\t        )\n251\t        result = apply_guess(state, \"Z\")\n252\t        self.assertIn(\"Z\", result.guessed_letters)\n253\t        self.assertTrue(result.game_over)\n254\t        self.assertFalse(result.won)\n255\t        self.assertEqual(result.remaining_water, 0)\n256\t        self.assertEqual(result.weed_count, 6)\n257\t        self.assertEqual(result.status_message, MSG_LOSS_TEMPLATE.format(word=\"GARDEN\"))\n258\t        self.assertFalse(is_won(result))\n259\t        self.assertTrue(is_lost(result))\n260\t\n261\t    def test_guess_after_loss_is_noop(self):\n262\t        state = _make_state(game_over=True, won=False, remaining_water=0, weed_count=6)\n263\t        result = apply_guess(state, \"A\")\n264\t        self.assertEqual(result.remaining_water, 0)\n265\t        self.assertEqual(result.weed_count, 6)\n266\t        self.assertTrue(result.game_over)\n267\t        self.assertFalse(result.won)\n268\t        self.assertEqual(result.status_message, MSG_GAME_OVER)\n269\t\n270\t\n271\tclass TestApplyGuessImmutability(unittest.TestCase):\n272\t    def test_original_state_not_mutated_on_correct_guess(self):\n273\t        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\")\n274\t        original_guessed = frozenset(state.guessed_letters)\n275\t        original_water = state.remaining_water\n276\t        apply_guess(state, \"G\")\n277\t        self.assertEqual(state.guessed_letters, original_guessed)\n278\t        self.assertEqual(state.remaining_water, original_water)\n279\t\n280\t    def test_original_state_not_mutated_on_wrong_guess(self):\n281\t        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\")\n282\t        original_guessed = frozenset(state.guessed_letters)\n283\t        original_water = state.remaining_water\n284\t        apply_guess(state, \"Z\")\n285\t        self.assertEqual(state.guessed_letters, original_guessed)\n286\t        self.assertEqual(state.remaining_water, original_water)\n287\t\n288\t\n289\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n290\t# display_word — Test 9\n291\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n292\t\n293\tclass TestDisplayWord(unittest.TestCase):\n294\t    # Test 9: The displayed word masks unguessed letters.\n295\t\n296\t    def test_all_unguessed_shows_blanks(self):\n297\t        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\", guessed_letters=set())\n298\t        self.assertEqual(display_word(state), \"_ _ _ _ _ _\")\n299\t\n300\t    def test_some_guessed_shows_mixed(self):\n301\t        # GARDEN: G(0) A(1) R(2) D(3) E(4) N(5) — G and R guessed\n302\t        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\", guessed_letters={\"G\", \"R\"})\n303\t        self.assertEqual(display_word(state), \"G _ R _ _ _\")\n304\t\n305\t    def test_all_guessed_shows_full_word(self):\n306\t        state = _make_state(\n307\t            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n308\t            guessed_letters={\"G\", \"A\", \"R\", \"D\", \"E\", \"N\"},\n309\t        )\n310\t        self.assertEqual(display_word(state), \"G A R D E N\")\n311\t\n312\t    def test_single_letter_word(self):\n313\t        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"A\", guessed_letters=set())\n314\t        self.assertEqual(display_word(state), \"_\")\n315\t\n316\t    def test_single_letter_word_guessed(self):\n317\t        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"A\", guessed_letters={\"A\"})\n318\t        self.assertEqual(display_word(state), \"A\")\n319\t\n320\t\n321\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n322\t# is_won / is_lost\n323\t# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n324\t\n325\tclass TestIsWonIsLost(unittest.TestCase):\n326\t    def test_is_won_false_when_incomplete(self):\n327\t        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\", guessed_letters={\"G\"})\n328\t        self.assertFalse(is_won(state))\n329\t\n330\t    def test_is_won_true_when_all_letters_guessed(self):\n331\t        state = _make_state(\n332\t            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n333\t            guessed_letters={\"G\", \"A\", \"R\", \"D\", \"E\", \"N\"},\n334\t        )\n335\t        self.assertTrue(is_won(state))\n336\t\n337\t    def test_is_won_true_with_extra_guessed_letters(self):\n338\t        # Extra wrong guesses don't prevent a win\n339\t        state = _make_state(\n340\t            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n341\t            guessed_letters={\"G\", \"A\", \"R\", \"D\", \"E\", \"N\", \"Z\", \"X\"},\n342\t        )\n343\t        self.assertTrue(is_won(state))\n344\t\n345\t    def test_is_lost_false_when_water_remains(self):\n346\t        state = _make_state(remaining_water=1)\n347\t        self.assertFalse(is_lost(state))\n348\t\n349\t    def test_is_lost_true_when_water_zero_and_not_won(self):\n350\t        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\", remaining_water=0, guessed_letters=set())\n351\t        self.assertTrue(is_lost(state))\n352\t\n353\t    def test_is_lost_false_when_won_despite_zero_water(self):\n354\t        # Logically shouldn't happen in normal play, but the predicate should be correct\n355\t        state = _make_state(\n356\t            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n357\t            guessed_letters={\"G\", \"A\", \"R\", \"D\", \"E\", \"N\"},\n358\t            remaining_water=0,\n359\t        )\n360\t        self.assertFalse(is_lost(state))\n361\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09d2d379-4cbc-4745-9b7a-9acf62397c86","uuid":"13eccc78-65de-42f0-9994-9650bc6bf11e","timestamp":"2026-06-12T03:46:43.528Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/task-002-w3/tests/test_game.py","content":"import random\nimport unittest\n\nfrom word_garden.game import (\n    GameState,\n    apply_guess,\n    display_word,\n    is_lost,\n    is_won,\n    new_game,\n    validate_guess,\n    MSG_ALREADY_GUESSED_TEMPLATE,\n    MSG_CORRECT,\n    MSG_GAME_OVER,\n    MSG_INCORRECT,\n    MSG_INVALID_NOT_LETTER,\n    MSG_INVALID_NOT_SINGLE,\n    MSG_LOSS_TEMPLATE,\n    MSG_WIN_TEMPLATE,\n)\n\n\ndef _make_state(**kwargs) -> GameState:\n    \"\"\"Build a GameState with sensible defaults, overridden by kwargs.\"\"\"\n    defaults = dict(\n        secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n        guessed_letters=set(),\n        remaining_water=6,\n        weed_count=0,\n        max_water=6,\n    )\n    defaults.update(kwargs)\n    return GameState(**defaults)\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# new_game\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nclass TestNewGame(unittest.TestCase):\n    def test_initial_state_fields(self):\n        rng = random.Random(42)\n        state = new_game(\"normal\", rng=rng)\n        self.assertIsInstance(state.secret_word, str)\n        self.assertTrue(state.secret_word.isupper())\n        self.assertEqual(state.guessed_letters, set())\n        self.assertEqual(state.remaining_water, 6)\n        self.assertEqual(state.max_water, 6)\n        self.assertEqual(state.weed_count, 0)\n        self.assertEqual(state.status_message, \"\")\n        self.assertFalse(state.game_over)\n        self.assertFalse(state.won)\n\n    def test_easy_water_level(self):\n        state = new_game(\"easy\", rng=random.Random(1))\n        self.assertEqual(state.remaining_water, 8)\n        self.assertEqual(state.max_water, 8)\n\n    def test_hard_water_level(self):\n        state = new_game(\"hard\", rng=random.Random(1))\n        self.assertEqual(state.remaining_water, 4)\n        self.assertEqual(state.max_water, 4)\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# validate_guess — Test 5 (invalid input) and Test 6 (lowercase normalised)\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nclass TestValidateGuess(unittest.TestCase):\n    # Test 5: Invalid input is rejected with a specific message.\n\n    def test_empty_string_rejected(self):\n        letter, msg = validate_guess(\"\")\n        self.assertIsNone(letter)\n        self.assertEqual(msg, MSG_INVALID_NOT_SINGLE)\n\n    def test_whitespace_only_rejected(self):\n        letter, msg = validate_guess(\"   \")\n        self.assertIsNone(letter)\n        self.assertEqual(msg, MSG_INVALID_NOT_SINGLE)\n\n    def test_multiple_letters_rejected(self):\n        letter, msg = validate_guess(\"AB\")\n        self.assertIsNone(letter)\n        self.assertEqual(msg, MSG_INVALID_NOT_SINGLE)\n\n    def test_word_rejected(self):\n        letter, msg = validate_guess(\"apple\")\n        self.assertIsNone(letter)\n        self.assertEqual(msg, MSG_INVALID_NOT_SINGLE)\n\n    def test_digit_rejected(self):\n        letter, msg = validate_guess(\"7\")\n        self.assertIsNone(letter)\n        self.assertEqual(msg, MSG_INVALID_NOT_LETTER)\n\n    def test_symbol_rejected(self):\n        letter, msg = validate_guess(\"!\")\n        self.assertIsNone(letter)\n        self.assertEqual(msg, MSG_INVALID_NOT_LETTER)\n\n    # Test 6: Lowercase input is normalised to uppercase.\n\n    def test_lowercase_normalised(self):\n        letter, msg = validate_guess(\"a\")\n        self.assertEqual(letter, \"A\")\n        self.assertEqual(msg, \"\")\n\n    def test_leading_trailing_spaces_stripped(self):\n        letter, msg = validate_guess(\"  b  \")\n        self.assertEqual(letter, \"B\")\n        self.assertEqual(msg, \"\")\n\n    def test_valid_uppercase_accepted(self):\n        letter, msg = validate_guess(\"Z\")\n        self.assertEqual(letter, \"Z\")\n        self.assertEqual(msg, \"\")\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# apply_guess — Tests 1–4, 7–8\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nclass TestApplyGuessCorrect(unittest.TestCase):\n    # Test 1: A correct guess reveals matching letters.\n\n    def test_correct_guess_adds_letter_to_guessed(self):\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\")\n        result = apply_guess(state, \"G\")\n        self.assertIn(\"G\", result.guessed_letters)\n        self.assertEqual(result.remaining_water, 6)\n        self.assertEqual(result.weed_count, 0)\n        self.assertEqual(result.status_message, MSG_CORRECT)\n        self.assertFalse(result.game_over)\n        self.assertFalse(result.won)\n\n    def test_correct_guess_display_reveals_letter(self):\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\")\n        result = apply_guess(state, \"G\")\n        # GARDEN with only G revealed → G _ _ _ _ _\n        self.assertEqual(display_word(result), \"G _ _ _ _ _\")\n\n    def test_correct_guess_recurring_letter_all_positions_revealed(self):\n        # SEEDLING has two E's; both should appear in display\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"SEEDLING\")\n        result = apply_guess(state, \"E\")\n        self.assertIn(\"E\", result.guessed_letters)\n        displayed = display_word(result)\n        parts = displayed.split(\" \")\n        self.assertEqual(parts[1], \"E\")  # index 1 in SEEDLING\n        self.assertEqual(parts[2], \"E\")  # index 2 in SEEDLING\n\n\nclass TestApplyGuessIncorrect(unittest.TestCase):\n    # Tests 2 & 3: An incorrect guess reduces water by one and adds one weed.\n\n    def test_incorrect_guess_water_weed_letter(self):\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\")\n        result = apply_guess(state, \"Z\")\n        self.assertIn(\"Z\", result.guessed_letters)\n        self.assertEqual(result.remaining_water, 5)\n        self.assertEqual(result.weed_count, 1)\n        self.assertEqual(result.status_message, MSG_INCORRECT)\n        self.assertFalse(result.game_over)\n        self.assertFalse(result.won)\n\n    def test_incorrect_guess_exact_decrements(self):\n        state = _make_state(remaining_water=4, weed_count=2)\n        result = apply_guess(state, \"Z\")\n        self.assertEqual(result.remaining_water, 3)\n        self.assertEqual(result.weed_count, 3)\n\n\nclass TestApplyGuessRepeated(unittest.TestCase):\n    # Test 4: Repeated guesses do not reduce water or weeds.\n\n    def test_repeated_correct_letter_no_change(self):\n        state = _make_state(\n            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n            guessed_letters={\"G\"},\n            remaining_water=6,\n            weed_count=0,\n        )\n        result = apply_guess(state, \"G\")\n        self.assertEqual(result.remaining_water, 6)\n        self.assertEqual(result.weed_count, 0)\n        self.assertEqual(result.guessed_letters, {\"G\"})\n        self.assertEqual(\n            result.status_message,\n            MSG_ALREADY_GUESSED_TEMPLATE.format(letter=\"G\"),\n        )\n        self.assertFalse(result.game_over)\n        self.assertFalse(result.won)\n\n    def test_repeated_wrong_letter_no_change(self):\n        state = _make_state(\n            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n            guessed_letters={\"Z\"},\n            remaining_water=5,\n            weed_count=1,\n        )\n        result = apply_guess(state, \"Z\")\n        self.assertEqual(result.remaining_water, 5)\n        self.assertEqual(result.weed_count, 1)\n        self.assertEqual(result.guessed_letters, {\"Z\"})\n        self.assertEqual(\n            result.status_message,\n            MSG_ALREADY_GUESSED_TEMPLATE.format(letter=\"Z\"),\n        )\n\n\nclass TestApplyGuessWin(unittest.TestCase):\n    # Test 7: The game detects a win.\n\n    def test_win_on_last_letter(self):\n        state = _make_state(\n            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n            guessed_letters={\"G\", \"A\", \"R\", \"D\", \"E\"},\n            remaining_water=6,\n            weed_count=0,\n        )\n        result = apply_guess(state, \"N\")\n        self.assertIn(\"N\", result.guessed_letters)\n        self.assertTrue(result.game_over)\n        self.assertTrue(result.won)\n        self.assertEqual(result.remaining_water, 6)\n        self.assertEqual(result.weed_count, 0)\n        self.assertEqual(result.status_message, MSG_WIN_TEMPLATE.format(word=\"GARDEN\"))\n        self.assertTrue(is_won(result))\n        self.assertFalse(is_lost(result))\n\n    def test_guess_after_win_is_noop(self):\n        state = _make_state(game_over=True, won=True, remaining_water=6, weed_count=0)\n        result = apply_guess(state, \"X\")\n        self.assertEqual(result.remaining_water, 6)\n        self.assertEqual(result.weed_count, 0)\n        self.assertTrue(result.game_over)\n        self.assertTrue(result.won)\n        self.assertEqual(result.status_message, MSG_GAME_OVER)\n\n\nclass TestApplyGuessLoss(unittest.TestCase):\n    # Test 8: The game detects a loss.\n\n    def test_loss_on_final_water(self):\n        state = _make_state(\n            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n            remaining_water=1,\n            weed_count=5,\n        )\n        result = apply_guess(state, \"Z\")\n        self.assertIn(\"Z\", result.guessed_letters)\n        self.assertTrue(result.game_over)\n        self.assertFalse(result.won)\n        self.assertEqual(result.remaining_water, 0)\n        self.assertEqual(result.weed_count, 6)\n        self.assertEqual(result.status_message, MSG_LOSS_TEMPLATE.format(word=\"GARDEN\"))\n        self.assertFalse(is_won(result))\n        self.assertTrue(is_lost(result))\n\n    def test_guess_after_loss_is_noop(self):\n        state = _make_state(game_over=True, won=False, remaining_water=0, weed_count=6)\n        result = apply_guess(state, \"A\")\n        self.assertEqual(result.remaining_water, 0)\n        self.assertEqual(result.weed_count, 6)\n        self.assertTrue(result.game_over)\n        self.assertFalse(result.won)\n        self.assertEqual(result.status_message, MSG_GAME_OVER)\n\n\nclass TestApplyGuessImmutability(unittest.TestCase):\n    def test_original_state_not_mutated_on_correct_guess(self):\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\")\n        original_guessed = frozenset(state.guessed_letters)\n        original_water = state.remaining_water\n        apply_guess(state, \"G\")\n        self.assertEqual(state.guessed_letters, original_guessed)\n        self.assertEqual(state.remaining_water, original_water)\n\n    def test_original_state_not_mutated_on_wrong_guess(self):\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\")\n        original_guessed = frozenset(state.guessed_letters)\n        original_water = state.remaining_water\n        apply_guess(state, \"Z\")\n        self.assertEqual(state.guessed_letters, original_guessed)\n        self.assertEqual(state.remaining_water, original_water)\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# display_word — Test 9\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nclass TestDisplayWord(unittest.TestCase):\n    # Test 9: The displayed word masks unguessed letters.\n\n    def test_all_unguessed_shows_blanks(self):\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\", guessed_letters=set())\n        self.assertEqual(display_word(state), \"_ _ _ _ _ _\")\n\n    def test_some_guessed_shows_mixed(self):\n        # GARDEN: G(0) A(1) R(2) D(3) E(4) N(5) — G and R guessed\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\", guessed_letters={\"G\", \"R\"})\n        self.assertEqual(display_word(state), \"G _ R _ _ _\")\n\n    def test_all_guessed_shows_full_word(self):\n        state = _make_state(\n            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n            guessed_letters={\"G\", \"A\", \"R\", \"D\", \"E\", \"N\"},\n        )\n        self.assertEqual(display_word(state), \"G A R D E N\")\n\n    def test_single_letter_word(self):\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"A\", guessed_letters=set())\n        self.assertEqual(display_word(state), \"_\")\n\n    def test_single_letter_word_guessed(self):\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"A\", guessed_letters={\"A\"})\n        self.assertEqual(display_word(state), \"A\")\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# is_won / is_lost\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nclass TestIsWonIsLost(unittest.TestCase):\n    def test_is_won_false_when_incomplete(self):\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\", guessed_letters={\"G\"})\n        self.assertFalse(is_won(state))\n\n    def test_is_won_true_when_all_letters_guessed(self):\n        state = _make_state(\n            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n            guessed_letters={\"G\", \"A\", \"R\", \"D\", \"E\", \"N\"},\n        )\n        self.assertTrue(is_won(state))\n\n    def test_is_won_true_with_extra_guessed_letters(self):\n        # Extra wrong guesses don't prevent a win\n        state = _make_state(\n            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n            guessed_letters={\"G\", \"A\", \"R\", \"D\", \"E\", \"N\", \"Z\", \"X\"},\n        )\n        self.assertTrue(is_won(state))\n\n    def test_is_lost_false_when_water_remains(self):\n        state = _make_state(remaining_water=1)\n        self.assertFalse(is_lost(state))\n\n    def test_is_lost_true_when_water_zero_and_not_won(self):\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\", remaining_water=0, guessed_letters=set())\n        self.assertTrue(is_lost(state))\n\n    def test_is_lost_false_when_won_despite_zero_water(self):\n        # Logically shouldn't happen in normal play, but the predicate should be correct\n        state = _make_state(\n            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n            guessed_letters={\"G\", \"A\", \"R\", \"D\", \"E\", \"N\"},\n            remaining_water=0,\n        )\n        self.assertFalse(is_lost(state))\n","numLines":361,"startLine":1,"totalLines":361}}},{"type":"system","subtype":"thinking_tokens","estimated_tokens":1,"estimated_tokens_delta":1,"uuid":"361d5ca0-253c-4353-8594-452bef44ea49","session_id":"09d2d379-4cbc-4745-9b7a-9acf62397c86"},{"type":"system","subtype":"thinking_tokens","estimated_tokens":23,"estimated_tokens_de