817254c3603","session_id":"09d2d379-4cbc-4745-9b7a-9acf62397c86"},{"type":"system","subtype":"thinking_tokens","estimated_tokens":2011,"estimated_tokens_delta":1,"uuid":"022c4b61-0c90-4a2b-9099-07170aa40b5d","session_id":"09d2d379-4cbc-4745-9b7a-9acf62397c86"},{"type":"system","subtype":"thinking_tokens","estimated_tokens":2031,"estimated_tokens_delta":20,"uuid":"ab60abb7-60f5-4550-8b3c-8470e555a125","session_id":"09d2d379-4cbc-4745-9b7a-9acf62397c86"},{"type":"system","subtype":"thinking_tokens","estimated_tokens":2050,"estimated_tokens_delta":19,"uuid":"c7773aa8-918f-4b18-a7bd-8cc2275a6579","session_id":"09d2d379-4cbc-4745-9b7a-9acf62397c86"},{"type":"system","subtype":"thinking_tokens","estimated_tokens":6942,"estimated_tokens_delta":4892,"uuid":"2ad79f9f-7ece-4782-9c3e-c00a477ef9fd","session_id":"09d2d379-4cbc-4745-9b7a-9acf62397c86"},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_014ZztNa1dETiP9x5Ji4NVER","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture of what to implement. Let me write all the files.\n\nKey design decisions:\n1. **ui.py** - Pure rendering, no I/O. Growth stages based on fraction of word revealed.\n2. **main.py** - Only I/O module. Uses injectable input_fn/output_fn for testability.\n3. **__main__.py** - Simple entry point.\n4. **tests/test_ui.py** - Tests for all UI functions + end-to-end tests.\n5. **README.md** - Project description.\n\nLet me implement these now.\nI'm working out the growth stage logic: the plant starts dormant with no letters revealed, progresses as the player guesses more letters, reaches near-win status once 60% of unique letters are exposed, and transitions to either victory or defeat based on the game outcome. For the output format, I need to render the title, plant status, masked word, guessed letters in sorted order, water count with symbols, and weed count with symbols.\n\nFor the display modes, emoji uses water droplets and leaf symbols while ASCII mode substitutes bracket-enclosed text like `[****]` for water and `[--]` for weeds, with stage visuals represented as `[seed]`, `[plant]`, `[bud]`, `[flower]`, or `[wilted]`. I'm also checking the alignment in the spec examples to ensure the labels and values line up properly.\n\nNow I'm looking at the win and loss screen formats—the win screen shows a bloom emoji or `[flower]` with \"You guessed the word\" and a thriving garden message, while the loss screen displays a wilted emoji or `[wilted]` with the word reveal and an encouragement to try again. I need to implement these screens and then figure out how to structure the tests with injected game state.\n\nFor testing, I'll monkeypatch `new_game` to return a controlled state—for the win test, I'll set up a short word like \"CAT\" with full water remaining, feed in the correct letters, and verify the win screen appears. For the loss test, I'll use a word with minimal water remaining, input wrong letters to drain it completely, and check that the loss screen displays properly. Writing test helper... Adding test cases... I need to check how the monkeypatched `new_game` function gets called in the test, since I'm passing `--ascii` as an argument but the patched version will use the default difficulty. The key is making sure the test setup aligns with what `main()` actually does when it invokes `new_game`.\n\nNow I'm planning out the test file structure: I'll need a helper to create game state, then test classes for emoji rendering, ASCII rendering, all five growth stages, win and loss screens, and an end-to-end test covering both victory and defeat paths. After that, I'll write the actual implementation files starting with ui.py, where I need to define the message strings for the end screens.\n\nI should define all the user-facing text as module-level constants in ui.py—things like the title, win/loss headers, and messages—so every other module and test can import them instead of duplicating the strings. I'll also need constants for each growth stage visual.\n\nNow I'm thinking through the render format more carefully. Water and weeds always need both a text label and a count, plus their symbols—so in emoji mode it's `Water: 4/6 💧💧💧💧` and in ASCII mode it's `Water: 4/6 [****]`. For weeds, I'm deciding whether to show empty brackets when the count is zero or just omit the symbols entirely.\n\nLooking at the spec examples, when there are no weeds I should show `Weeds: 0` without symbols in emoji mode, and in ASCII mode I could either show `Weeds: 0 []` with empty brackets or just `Weeds: 0`—the empty brackets make it clearer that the format is consistent even when there's nothing to display. I'm going back to the spec example to keep things simple—just show the count with symbols when there's something to display, and for zero counts in ASCII mode, use empty brackets to maintain consistency. I need to clarify the render format by checking the spec examples more carefully. The growth stage icon appears in the title line in the spec example, but the task description suggests displaying plant/garden status separately. Let me structure the output as: title (\"Word Garden\"), growth stage on its own line, then the word, guessed letters, water count, weeds count, and the status message from the previous turn. them on separate lines. But looking at the SPEC examples more carefully, the growth stage emoji is integrated into the title itself—`🌱 Word Garden`, `🌿 Word Garden`, etc.—rather than appearing as a separate status line. The task brief mentions showing plant/garden status, but the SPEC format suggests embedding the stage glyph directly in the title. Let me check the stage progression table to confirm the emoji mappings: starting with 🌱, then 🌿 for progress, 🌷 near win, and 🌻 at win. I'm settling on keeping the title static as \"🌱 Word Garden\" and then showing the current plant stage separately below it, so there's no emoji repetition. The plant status line will display the appropriate glyph based on the game state—whether it's early progress, near winning, or other mid-game stages. the current growth stage glyph. For the water and weed display, I'm formatting them with proper alignment—showing the filled indicators (droplets or brackets) matching the current count, and handling edge cases like zero weeds or zero water by adjusting what symbols appear.\n\nNow I'm ready to write the implementation, making sure the tests verify that emoji mode displays the water count with actual emoji symbols while ASCII mode uses bracket characters, and that ASCII output contains no non-ASCII characters. The loop structure is correct—after the game ends, we exit and show the end screen without rendering the final board state again, which matches the spec. Now I'm ready to write the main function.\n\nFor the re-prompt on invalid input, I'll stick with the same \"Guess a letter: \" prompt for consistency. I'm considering two approaches: an inner loop that keeps prompting until valid input is received, or an outer loop with a continue statement to skip the rest of the iteration. The inner loop approach is cleaner since it keeps the validation logic self-contained. Option A keeps things cleaner—the user sees the validation error inline without unnecessary re-rendering, while the board still displays the previous turn's feedback. Now I'm writing the rendering functions for the UI module, focusing on clean, well-named functions that return strings without handling any I/O directly.\n\nI'm defining module-level constants for all user-facing strings like titles, win/loss messages, and emoji symbols so tests can import them rather than duplicating literals throughout the code.\n\nNow I'm setting up a dictionary that maps game growth stages to their emoji and ASCII representations, ranging from seed to wilted flower, along with a threshold for determining when the player is close to winning based on the fraction of unique letters they've revealed.\n\nDefining helper functions to retrieve the appropriate glyph based on the game mode and to generate water and weed symbols... Writing screen display functions...\n\nI'm noticing there's a redundant helper function that I'm not actually using in the render logic, so I should clean that up and just reference the data directly where needed.\n\nFor the water display formatting, I need to verify how it looks across different scenarios—when there's water versus when the tank is empty, and how the spacing works in both emoji and ASCII modes. There's a trailing space issue I should address when the water count is zero.\n\nI'm refactoring the water symbols function to handle this more cleanly: for ASCII mode, always show the brackets even when empty, but for emoji mode, only include the emoji characters when there's actual water to display. This way the format stays consistent and testable. Now I'm setting up the test file with the necessary imports from the game module, UI rendering functions, and the main entry point for end-to-end testing.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":10844,"cache_read_input_tokens":34343,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":10844},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09d2d379-4cbc-4745-9b7a-9acf62397c86","uuid":"588ada9a-785b-43de-9e03-6fd015859191","request_id":"req_011CbxgPJMdhaG2GmE6dyK4X"},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_014ZztNa1dETiP9x5Ji4NVER","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a clear picture. Let me implement all five files."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":10844,"cache_read_input_tokens":34343,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":10844},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09d2d379-4cbc-4745-9b7a-9acf62397c86","uuid":"725e5664-ddeb-4d57-9db6-fff8863989b0","request_id":"req_011CbxgPJMdhaG2GmE6dyK4X"},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_014ZztNa1dETiP9x5Ji4NVER","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01JKkN8zPwvC19Ga8NSZeQdS","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/task-002-w3/word_garden/ui.py","content":"\"\"\"Rendering functions for Word Garden. No I/O — every function returns a string.\"\"\"\n\nfrom .game import GameState, display_word\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# User-facing string constants.\n# Tests MUST import these rather than re-typing literals.\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nTITLE_EMOJI = \"🌱 Word Garden\"\nTITLE_ASCII = \"* Word Garden\"\n\nWIN_HEADER_EMOJI = \"🌻 Bloom!\"\nWIN_HEADER_ASCII = \"[flower] Bloom!\"\nWIN_WORD_PREFIX = \"You guessed the word: \"\nWIN_BODY = \"The garden is thriving.\"\n\nLOSS_HEADER_EMOJI = \"🥀 The garden ran out of water.\"\nLOSS_HEADER_ASCII = \"[wilted] The garden ran out of water.\"\nLOSS_WORD_PREFIX = \"The word was: \"\nLOSS_BODY = \"Try again and grow a new garden.\"\n\nWATER_EMOJI = \"💧\"\nWEED_EMOJI = \"🌿\"\n\n# Growth stage glyphs: stage name → (emoji, ascii)\n_STAGE_GLYPHS: dict[str, tuple[str, str]] = {\n    \"start\":    (\"🌱\", \"[seed]\"),\n    \"progress\": (\"🌿\", \"[plant]\"),\n    \"near_win\": (\"🌷\", \"[bud]\"),\n    \"win\":      (\"🌻\", \"[flower]\"),\n    \"loss\":     (\"🥀\", \"[wilted]\"),\n}\n\n_NEAR_WIN_THRESHOLD = 0.6\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Helpers\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\ndef _growth_stage(state: GameState) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Return the current growth stage key based on state.\"\"\"\n    if state.won:\n        return \"win\"\n    if state.game_over:\n        return \"loss\"\n    unique = set(state.secret_word)\n    if not unique:\n        return \"start\"\n    revealed = len(unique & state.guessed_letters) / len(unique)\n    if revealed == 0:\n        return \"start\"\n    if revealed >= _NEAR_WIN_THRESHOLD:\n        return \"near_win\"\n    return \"progress\"\n\n\ndef _water_symbols(count: int, ascii_mode: bool) -> str:\n    if ascii_mode:\n        return f\"[{'*' * count}]\"\n    return WATER_EMOJI * count  # empty string when count is 0\n\n\ndef _weed_symbols(count: int, ascii_mode: bool) -> str:\n    if ascii_mode:\n        return f\"[{'-' * count}]\"\n    return WEED_EMOJI * count  # empty string when count is 0\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Public rendering functions\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\ndef render(state: GameState, ascii_mode: bool = False) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Return the full turn display as a string.\n\n    Order: title, growth-stage visual, masked word, guessed letters,\n    water, weeds, and (if non-empty) the previous turn's status_message.\n    \"\"\"\n    title = TITLE_ASCII if ascii_mode else TITLE_EMOJI\n\n    stage = _growth_stage(state)\n    emoji_glyph, ascii_glyph = _STAGE_GLYPHS[stage]\n    stage_visual = ascii_glyph if ascii_mode else emoji_glyph\n\n    word_display = display_word(state)\n    guessed = \" \".join(sorted(state.guessed_letters))\n\n    # Water line: always shows count/max and symbols (empty brackets in ASCII when 0)\n    water_symbols = _water_symbols(state.remaining_water, ascii_mode)\n    water_line = f\"Water:    {state.remaining_water}/{state.max_water}\"\n    if water_symbols:\n        water_line += f\" {water_symbols}\"\n\n    # Weed line: shows count and symbols when count > 0\n    weed_symbols = _weed_symbols(state.weed_count, ascii_mode) if state.weed_count > 0 else \"\"\n    weed_line = f\"Weeds:    {state.weed_count}\"\n    if weed_symbols:\n        weed_line += f\" {weed_symbols}\"\n\n    lines = [\n        title,\n        \"\",\n        stage_visual,\n        \"\",\n        f\"Word:     {word_display}\",\n        f\"Guessed:  {guessed}\",\n        water_line,\n        weed_line,\n    ]\n\n    if state.status_message:\n        lines.extend([\"\", state.status_message])\n\n    return \"\\n\".join(lines)\n\n\ndef win_screen(state: GameState, ascii_mode: bool = False) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Return the win end-screen as a string (SPEC §6.6).\"\"\"\n    header = WIN_HEADER_ASCII if ascii_mode else WIN_HEADER_EMOJI\n    return \"\\n\".join([\n        header,\n        \"\",\n        f\"{WIN_WORD_PREFIX}{state.secret_word}\",\n        WIN_BODY,\n    ])\n\n\ndef loss_screen(state: GameState, ascii_mode: bool = False) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Return the loss end-screen as a string, revealing the secret word (SPEC §6.7).\"\"\"\n    header = LOSS_HEADER_ASCII if ascii_mode else LOSS_HEADER_EMOJI\n    return \"\\n\".join([\n        header,\n        \"\",\n        f\"{LOSS_WORD_PREFIX}{state.secret_word}\",\n        LOSS_BODY,\n    ])\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":10844,"cache_read_input_tokens":34343,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":10844},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09d2d379-4cbc-4745-9b7a-9acf62397c86","uuid":"0f05e959-353e-403e-a961-19ce95fcf7ab","request_id":"req_011CbxgPJMdhaG2GmE6dyK4X"},{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JKkN8zPwvC19Ga8NSZeQdS","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/task-002-w3/word_garden/ui.py (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09d2d379-4cbc-4745-9b7a-9acf62397c86","uuid":"c0a03f02-1ed5-4bfb-8ccf-9e07481ed2a5","timestamp":"2026-06-12T03:49:17.269Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/task-002-w3/word_garden/ui.py","content":"\"\"\"Rendering functions for Word Garden. No I/O — every function returns a string.\"\"\"\n\nfrom .game import GameState, display_word\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# User-facing string constants.\n# Tests MUST import these rather than re-typing literals.\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nTITLE_EMOJI = \"🌱 Word Garden\"\nTITLE_ASCII = \"* Word Garden\"\n\nWIN_HEADER_EMOJI = \"🌻 Bloom!\"\nWIN_HEADER_ASCII = \"[flower] Bloom!\"\nWIN_WORD_PREFIX = \"You guessed the word: \"\nWIN_BODY = \"The garden is thriving.\"\n\nLOSS_HEADER_EMOJI = \"🥀 The garden ran out of water.\"\nLOSS_HEADER_ASCII = \"[wilted] The garden ran out of water.\"\nLOSS_WORD_PREFIX = \"The word was: \"\nLOSS_BODY = \"Try again and grow a new garden.\"\n\nWATER_EMOJI = \"💧\"\nWEED_EMOJI = \"🌿\"\n\n# Growth stage glyphs: stage name → (emoji, ascii)\n_STAGE_GLYPHS: dict[str, tuple[str, str]] = {\n    \"start\":    (\"🌱\", \"[seed]\"),\n    \"progress\": (\"🌿\", \"[plant]\"),\n    \"near_win\": (\"🌷\", \"[bud]\"),\n    \"win\":      (\"🌻\", \"[flower]\"),\n    \"loss\":     (\"🥀\", \"[wilted]\"),\n}\n\n_NEAR_WIN_THRESHOLD = 0.6\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Helpers\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\ndef _growth_stage(state: GameState) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Return the current growth stage key based on state.\"\"\"\n    if state.won:\n        return \"win\"\n    if state.game_over:\n        return \"loss\"\n    unique = set(state.secret_word)\n    if not unique:\n        return \"start\"\n    revealed = len(unique & state.guessed_letters) / len(unique)\n    if revealed == 0:\n        return \"start\"\n    if revealed >= _NEAR_WIN_THRESHOLD:\n        return \"near_win\"\n    return \"progress\"\n\n\ndef _water_symbols(count: int, ascii_mode: bool) -> str:\n    if ascii_mode:\n        return f\"[{'*' * count}]\"\n    return WATER_EMOJI * count  # empty string when count is 0\n\n\ndef _weed_symbols(count: int, ascii_mode: bool) -> str:\n    if ascii_mode:\n        return f\"[{'-' * count}]\"\n    return WEED_EMOJI * count  # empty string when count is 0\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Public rendering functions\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\ndef render(state: GameState, ascii_mode: bool = False) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Return the full turn display as a string.\n\n    Order: title, growth-stage visual, masked word, guessed letters,\n    water, weeds, and (if non-empty) the previous turn's status_message.\n    \"\"\"\n    title = TITLE_ASCII if ascii_mode else TITLE_EMOJI\n\n    stage = _growth_stage(state)\n    emoji_glyph, ascii_glyph = _STAGE_GLYPHS[stage]\n    stage_visual = ascii_glyph if ascii_mode else emoji_glyph\n\n    word_display = display_word(state)\n    guessed = \" \".join(sorted(state.guessed_letters))\n\n    # Water line: always shows count/max and symbols (empty brackets in ASCII when 0)\n    water_symbols = _water_symbols(state.remaining_water, ascii_mode)\n    water_line = f\"Water:    {state.remaining_water}/{state.max_water}\"\n    if water_symbols:\n        water_line += f\" {water_symbols}\"\n\n    # Weed line: shows count and symbols when count > 0\n    weed_symbols = _weed_symbols(state.weed_count, ascii_mode) if state.weed_count > 0 else \"\"\n    weed_line = f\"Weeds:    {state.weed_count}\"\n    if weed_symbols:\n        weed_line += f\" {weed_symbols}\"\n\n    lines = [\n        title,\n        \"\",\n        stage_visual,\n        \"\",\n        f\"Word:     {word_display}\",\n        f\"Guessed:  {guessed}\",\n        water_line,\n        weed_line,\n    ]\n\n    if state.status_message:\n        lines.extend([\"\", state.status_message])\n\n    return \"\\n\".join(lines)\n\n\ndef win_screen(state: GameState, ascii_mode: bool = False) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Return the win end-screen as a string (SPEC §6.6).\"\"\"\n    header = WIN_HEADER_ASCII if ascii_mode else WIN_HEADER_EMOJI\n    return \"\\n\".join([\n        header,\n        \"\",\n        f\"{WIN_WORD_PREFIX}{state.secret_word}\",\n        WIN_BODY,\n    ])\n\n\ndef loss_screen(state: GameState, ascii_mode: bool = False) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Return the loss end-screen as a string, revealing the secret word (SPEC §6.7).\"\"\"\n    header = LOSS_HEADER_ASCII if ascii_mode else LOSS_HEADER_EMOJI\n    return \"\\n\".join([\n        header,\n        \"\",\n        f\"{LOSS_WORD_PREFIX}{state.secret_word}\",\n        LOSS_BODY,\n    ])\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null,"userModified":false}},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_012Z2L5TdxPRi2nuSRRf4JMF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01HpQT1hs2spWsM6brPy9vfn","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/task-002-w3/word_garden/main.py","content":"\"\"\"Main game loop and entry point for Word Garden.\n\nThis is the only module that touches stdin/stdout. All output goes through\noutput_fn and all input through input_fn so the loop is fully testable.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport argparse\n\nfrom .game import apply_guess, new_game, validate_guess\nfrom .ui import loss_screen, render, win_screen\n\nGOODBYE_MESSAGE = \"\\nGoodbye! Come back soon to tend your garden.\"\n\n\ndef main(argv=None, input_fn=input, output_fn=print) -> int:\n    \"\"\"Run one complete game session. Returns 0 on clean exit.\"\"\"\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(\n        prog=\"word_garden\",\n        description=\"Word Garden — a friendly terminal word-guessing game.\",\n    )\n    parser.add_argument(\n        \"--difficulty\",\n        choices=[\"easy\", \"normal\", \"hard\"],\n        default=\"normal\",\n        help=\"Game difficulty (default: normal)\",\n    )\n    parser.add_argument(\n        \"--ascii\",\n        action=\"store_true\",\n        help=\"ASCII-only output — no emoji\",\n    )\n    args = parser.parse_args(argv)\n\n    state = new_game(difficulty=args.difficulty)\n\n    try:\n        while not state.game_over:\n            output_fn(render(state, ascii_mode=args.ascii))\n\n            # Inner loop: re-prompt on invalid input without re-rendering the board.\n            while True:\n                raw = input_fn(\"Guess a letter: \")\n                letter, error = validate_guess(raw)\n                if letter is not None:\n                    break\n                output_fn(error)\n\n            state = apply_guess(state, letter)\n\n        if state.won:\n            output_fn(win_screen(state, ascii_mode=args.ascii))\n        else:\n            output_fn(loss_screen(state, ascii_mode=args.ascii))\n\n    except (EOFError, KeyboardInterrupt):\n        output_fn(GOODBYE_MESSAGE)\n\n    return 0\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":10117,"cache_read_input_tokens":45187,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":10117},"output_tokens":64,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09d2d379-4cbc-4745-9b7a-9acf62397c86","uuid":"216de2c2-4c4b-4872-a2a0-9d3e49adde51","request_id":"req_011CbxgacvPrcUSAbhCpqyyZ"},{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HpQT1hs2spWsM6brPy9vfn","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/task-002-w3/word_garden/main.py (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09d2d379-4cbc-4745-9b7a-9acf62397c86","uuid":"8d9f88a1-14d6-4ebc-a1c3-34d2e26f32f7","timestamp":"2026-06-12T03:49:29.331Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/task-002-w3/word_garden/main.py","content":"\"\"\"Main game loop and entry point for Word Garden.\n\nThis is the only module that touches stdin/stdout. All output goes through\noutput_fn and all input through input_fn so the loop is fully testable.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport argparse\n\nfrom .game import apply_guess, new_game, validate_guess\nfrom .ui import loss_screen, render, win_screen\n\nGOODBYE_MESSAGE = \"\\nGoodbye! Come back soon to tend your garden.\"\n\n\ndef main(argv=None, input_fn=input, output_fn=print) -> int:\n    \"\"\"Run one complete game session. Returns 0 on clean exit.\"\"\"\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(\n        prog=\"word_garden\",\n        description=\"Word Garden — a friendly terminal word-guessing game.\",\n    )\n    parser.add_argument(\n        \"--difficulty\",\n        choices=[\"easy\", \"normal\", \"hard\"],\n        default=\"normal\",\n        help=\"Game difficulty (default: normal)\",\n    )\n    parser.add_argument(\n        \"--ascii\",\n        action=\"store_true\",\n        help=\"ASCII-only output — no emoji\",\n    )\n    args = parser.parse_args(argv)\n\n    state = new_game(difficulty=args.difficulty)\n\n    try:\n        while not state.game_over:\n            output_fn(render(state, ascii_mode=args.ascii))\n\n            # Inner loop: re-prompt on invalid input without re-rendering the board.\n            while True:\n                raw = input_fn(\"Guess a letter: \")\n                letter, error = validate_guess(raw)\n                if letter is not None:\n                    break\n                output_fn(error)\n\n            state = apply_guess(state, letter)\n\n        if state.won:\n            output_fn(win_screen(state, ascii_mode=args.ascii))\n        else:\n            output_fn(loss_screen(state, ascii_mode=args.ascii))\n\n    except (EOFError, KeyboardInterrupt):\n        output_fn(GOODBYE_MESSAGE)\n\n    return 0\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null,"userModified":false}},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01HZqQJCYw8tPUV7ojGtLpZ8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01RbAtToyeAhCxA2CohGef2C","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/task-002-w3/word_garden/__main__.py","content":"import sys\n\nfrom .main import main\n\nsys.exit(main())\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":642,"cache_read_input_tokens":55304,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":642},"output_tokens":58,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09d2d379-4cbc-4745-9b7a-9acf62397c86","uuid":"1184c8d6-012e-4060-89fc-11a63245e02a","request_id":"req_011CbxgbWPX5U5TaHQinP2ua"},{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RbAtToyeAhCxA2CohGef2C","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/task-002-w3/word_garden/__main__.py (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09d2d379-4cbc-4745-9b7a-9acf62397c86","uuid":"674e869b-073c-457a-955f-62455699345d","timestamp":"2026-06-12T03:49:32.006Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/task-002-w3/word_garden/__main__.py","content":"import sys\n\nfrom .main import main\n\nsys.exit(main())\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null,"userModified":false}},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01NFqFwoFiDYEKJVDfbnq7yv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now for the tests:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":176,"cache_read_input_tokens":55946,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":176},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09d2d379-4cbc-4745-9b7a-9acf62397c86","uuid":"7e712ab5-fdb0-48d3-9ff1-385eea10381d","request_id":"req_011Cbxgbhs5rNmtS3nRbTnfH"},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01NFqFwoFiDYEKJVDfbnq7yv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01HDzTssRKFj3Rdco4aea37r","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/task-002-w3/tests/test_ui.py","content":"import unittest\nfrom unittest.mock import patch\n\nfrom word_garden.game import GameState, MSG_CORRECT, MSG_INCORRECT\nfrom word_garden.main import GOODBYE_MESSAGE, main\nfrom word_garden.ui import (\n    LOSS_BODY,\n    LOSS_HEADER_ASCII,\n    LOSS_HEADER_EMOJI,\n    LOSS_WORD_PREFIX,\n    TITLE_ASCII,\n    TITLE_EMOJI,\n    WIN_BODY,\n    WIN_HEADER_ASCII,\n    WIN_HEADER_EMOJI,\n    WIN_WORD_PREFIX,\n    loss_screen,\n    render,\n    win_screen,\n)\n\n\ndef _make_state(**kwargs) -> GameState:\n    \"\"\"Build a GameState with sensible defaults, overridden by kwargs.\"\"\"\n    defaults = dict(\n        secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n        guessed_letters=set(),\n        remaining_water=6,\n        weed_count=0,\n        max_water=6,\n    )\n    defaults.update(kwargs)\n    return GameState(**defaults)\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# render — emoji mode\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nclass TestRenderEmojiMode(unittest.TestCase):\n    def test_contains_title(self):\n        state = _make_state()\n        output = render(state)\n        self.assertIn(TITLE_EMOJI, output)\n\n    def test_water_line_has_label_count_and_symbols(self):\n        state = _make_state(remaining_water=4, max_water=6)\n        output = render(state)\n        self.assertIn(\"Water:\", output)\n        self.assertIn(\"4/6\", output)\n        self.assertIn(\"💧💧💧💧\", output)\n\n    def test_weed_line_has_label_count_and_symbols(self):\n        state = _make_state(weed_count=2)\n        output = render(state)\n        self.assertIn(\"Weeds:\", output)\n        self.assertIn(\"2\", output)\n        self.assertIn(\"🌿🌿\", output)\n\n    def test_weed_line_shows_zero_when_no_weeds(self):\n        state = _make_state(weed_count=0)\n        output = render(state)\n        self.assertIn(\"Weeds:    0\", output)\n\n    def test_guessed_letters_sorted_space_separated(self):\n        state = _make_state(guessed_letters={\"E\", \"A\", \"R\"})\n        output = render(state)\n        self.assertIn(\"A E R\", output)\n\n    def test_masked_word_shown(self):\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"CAT\", guessed_letters={\"A\"})\n        output = render(state)\n        self.assertIn(\"_ A _\", output)\n\n    def test_status_message_included_when_present(self):\n        state = _make_state(status_message=MSG_CORRECT)\n        output = render(state)\n        self.assertIn(MSG_CORRECT, output)\n\n    def test_no_status_message_when_empty(self):\n        state = _make_state(status_message=\"\")\n        output = render(state)\n        self.assertNotIn(MSG_CORRECT, output)\n        self.assertNotIn(MSG_INCORRECT, output)\n\n    def test_output_order(self):\n        state = _make_state(\n            secret_word=\"CAT\",\n            guessed_letters={\"A\"},\n            remaining_water=4,\n            max_water=6,\n            weed_count=2,\n            status_message=MSG_CORRECT,\n        )\n        output = render(state)\n        title_pos = output.index(TITLE_EMOJI)\n        word_pos = output.index(\"Word:\")\n        guessed_pos = output.index(\"Guessed:\")\n        water_pos = output.index(\"Water:\")\n        weed_pos = output.index(\"Weeds:\")\n        msg_pos = output.index(MSG_CORRECT)\n        self.assertLess(title_pos, word_pos)\n        self.assertLess(word_pos, guessed_pos)\n        self.assertLess(guessed_pos, water_pos)\n        self.assertLess(water_pos, weed_pos)\n        self.assertLess(weed_pos, msg_pos)\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# render — ASCII mode\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nclass TestRenderAsciiMode(unittest.TestCase):\n    def test_title_is_ascii(self):\n        state = _make_state()\n        output = render(state, ascii_mode=True)\n        self.assertIn(TITLE_ASCII, output)\n        self.assertNotIn(TITLE_EMOJI, output)\n\n    def test_output_contains_no_non_ascii(self):\n        state = _make_state(\n            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n            guessed_letters={\"G\", \"A\"},\n            remaining_water=4,\n            max_water=6,\n            weed_count=2,\n            status_message=MSG_INCORRECT,\n        )\n        output = render(state, ascii_mode=True)\n        self.assertTrue(\n            output.isascii(),\n            f\"Non-ASCII characters found in ASCII render output:\\n{output!r}\",\n        )\n\n    def test_water_symbols_use_brackets(self):\n        state = _make_state(remaining_water=3, max_water=6)\n        output = render(state, ascii_mode=True)\n        self.assertIn(\"3/6 [***]\", output)\n\n    def test_weed_symbols_use_brackets(self):\n        state = _make_state(weed_count=2)\n        output = render(state, ascii_mode=True)\n        self.assertIn(\"2 [--]\", output)\n\n    def test_no_emoji_in_ascii_mode(self):\n        state = _make_state(weed_count=2, remaining_water=3)\n        output = render(state, ascii_mode=True)\n        self.assertNotIn(\"💧\", output)\n        self.assertNotIn(\"🌿\", output)\n        self.assertNotIn(\"🌱\", output)\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Growth stages\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nclass TestGrowthStages(unittest.TestCase):\n    def test_start_stage_when_no_letters_revealed(self):\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\", guessed_letters=set())\n        output = render(state, ascii_mode=True)\n        self.assertIn(\"[seed]\", output)\n\n    def test_progress_stage_when_some_letters_revealed(self):\n        # GARDEN has 6 unique letters; reveal 1 → 1/6 ≈ 17% (below 60%)\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\", guessed_letters={\"G\"})\n        output = render(state, ascii_mode=True)\n        self.assertIn(\"[plant]\", output)\n\n    def test_near_win_stage_when_most_letters_revealed(self):\n        # GARDEN: reveal 4 of 6 unique letters → 67% (above 60% threshold)\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\", guessed_letters={\"G\", \"A\", \"R\", \"D\"})\n        output = render(state, ascii_mode=True)\n        self.assertIn(\"[bud]\", output)\n\n    def test_win_stage_when_game_won(self):\n        state = _make_state(game_over=True, won=True)\n        output = render(state, ascii_mode=True)\n        self.assertIn(\"[flower]\", output)\n\n    def test_loss_stage_when_game_lost(self):\n        state = _make_state(game_over=True, won=False, remaining_water=0)\n        output = render(state, ascii_mode=True)\n        self.assertIn(\"[wilted]\", output)\n\n    def test_near_win_stage_exactly_at_threshold(self):\n        # \"AB\": 2 unique letters; reveal both → 100% > 60%\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"AB\", guessed_letters={\"A\", \"B\"})\n        # won would not be set on the state itself, just guessed_letters\n        # (we're testing the stage logic, not the full win flow)\n        output = render(state, ascii_mode=True)\n        self.assertIn(\"[bud]\", output)\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# win_screen and loss_screen\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nclass TestWinScreen(unittest.TestCase):\n    def test_emoji_mode_contains_header_and_word(self):\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\")\n        output = win_screen(state)\n        self.assertIn(WIN_HEADER_EMOJI, output)\n        self.assertIn(f\"{WIN_WORD_PREFIX}GARDEN\", output)\n        self.assertIn(WIN_BODY, output)\n\n    def test_ascii_mode_contains_header_and_word(self):\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\")\n        output = win_screen(state, ascii_mode=True)\n        self.assertIn(WIN_HEADER_ASCII, output)\n        self.assertIn(f\"{WIN_WORD_PREFIX}GARDEN\", output)\n        self.assertIn(WIN_BODY, output)\n\n    def test_ascii_mode_no_non_ascii_characters(self):\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\")\n        output = win_screen(state, ascii_mode=True)\n        self.assertTrue(output.isascii(), f\"Non-ASCII found in win_screen:\\n{output!r}\")\n\n    def test_emoji_mode_absent_in_ascii_win_screen(self):\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\")\n        output = win_screen(state, ascii_mode=True)\n        self.assertNotIn(WIN_HEADER_EMOJI, output)\n\n\nclass TestLossScreen(unittest.TestCase):\n    def test_emoji_mode_contains_header_and_word(self):\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\")\n        output = loss_screen(state)\n        self.assertIn(LOSS_HEADER_EMOJI, output)\n        self.assertIn(f\"{LOSS_WORD_PREFIX}GARDEN\", output)\n        self.assertIn(LOSS_BODY, output)\n\n    def test_ascii_mode_contains_header_and_word(self):\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\")\n        output = loss_screen(state, ascii_mode=True)\n        self.assertIn(LOSS_HEADER_ASCII, output)\n        self.assertIn(f\"{LOSS_WORD_PREFIX}GARDEN\", output)\n        self.assertIn(LOSS_BODY, output)\n\n    def test_ascii_mode_no_non_ascii_characters(self):\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\")\n        output = loss_screen(state, ascii_mode=True)\n        self.assertTrue(output.isascii(), f\"Non-ASCII found in loss_screen:\\n{output!r}\")\n\n    def test_loss_screen_reveals_secret_word(self):\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"PYTHON\")\n        output = loss_screen(state)\n        self.assertIn(\"PYTHON\", output)\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# End-to-end main() tests\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nclass TestMainEndToEnd(unittest.TestCase):\n    \"\"\"Scripted game runs using injected input/output functions.\"\"\"\n\n    def _run_main(self, initial_state, inputs, ascii_mode=False):\n        \"\"\"Run main() with a fixed initial state and scripted inputs.\"\"\"\n        outputs = []\n        input_iter = iter(inputs)\n\n        argv = [\"--ascii\"] if ascii_mode else []\n        with patch(\"word_garden.main.new_game\", return_value=initial_state):\n            exit_code = main(\n                argv=argv,\n                input_fn=lambda prompt=\"\": next(input_iter),\n                output_fn=outputs.append,\n            )\n\n        return exit_code, outputs\n\n    def test_win_scenario_shows_win_screen(self):\n        # \"CAT\": guess C, A, T → all letters revealed → win\n        initial = GameState(\n            secret_word=\"CAT\",\n            guessed_letters=set(),\n            remaining_water=6,\n            weed_count=0,\n            max_water=6,\n        )\n        exit_code, outputs = self._run_main(initial, [\"C\", \"A\", \"T\"], ascii_mode=True)\n\n        full_output = \"\\n\".join(outputs)\n        self.assertEqual(exit_code, 0)\n        self.assertIn(WIN_HEADER_ASCII, full_output)\n        self.assertIn(f\"{WIN_WORD_PREFIX}CAT\", full_output)\n        self.assertIn(WIN_BODY, full_output)\n\n    def test_loss_scenario_shows_loss_screen_with_word(self):\n        # \"GARDEN\" with 2 water: guess Z, X → both wrong → water runs out\n        initial = GameState(\n            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n            guessed_letters=set(),\n            remaining_water=2,\n            weed_count=0,\n            max_water=2,\n        )\n        exit_code, outputs = self._run_main(initial, [\"Z\", \"X\"], ascii_mode=True)\n\n        full_output = \"\\n\".join(outputs)\n        self.assertEqual(exit_code, 0)\n        self.assertIn(LOSS_HEADER_ASCII, full_output)\n        self.assertIn(f\"{LOSS_WORD_PREFIX}GARDEN\", full_output)\n        self.assertIn(LOSS_BODY, full_output)\n\n    def test_invalid_input_does_not_consume_turn(self):\n        # \"AB\": one wrong guess (Z) and one valid letter (B) — then A to win.\n        # If invalid input consumed a turn we would lose early.\n        initial = GameState(\n            secret_word=\"AB\",\n            guessed_letters=set(),\n            remaining_water=1,\n            weed_count=0,\n            max_water=1,\n        )\n        # \"7\" is invalid, \"A\" and \"B\" are valid wins\n        exit_code, outputs = self._run_main(initial, [\"7\", \"A\", \"B\"], ascii_mode=True)\n\n        full_output = \"\\n\".join(outputs)\n        self.assertEqual(exit_code, 0)\n        self.assertIn(WIN_HEADER_ASCII, full_output)\n\n    def test_eof_exits_cleanly(self):\n        initial = _make_state()\n        outputs = []\n\n        with patch(\"word_garden.main.new_game\", return_value=initial):\n            exit_code = main(\n                argv=[\"--ascii\"],\n                input_fn=lambda prompt=\"\": (_ for _ in ()).throw(EOFError()),\n                output_fn=outputs.append,\n            )\n\n        self.assertEqual(exit_code, 0)\n        self.assertIn(GOODBYE_MESSAGE, \"\\n\".join(outputs))\n\n    def test_keyboard_interrupt_exits_cleanly(self):\n        initial = _make_state()\n        outputs = []\n\n        with patch(\"word_garden.main.new_game\", return_value=initial):\n            exit_code = main(\n                argv=[\"--ascii\"],\n                input_fn=lambda prompt=\"\": (_ for _ in ()).throw(KeyboardInterrupt()),\n                output_fn=outputs.append,\n            )\n\n        self.assertEqual(exit_code, 0)\n        self.assertIn(GOODBYE_MESSAGE, \"\\n\".join(outputs))\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":176,"cache_read_input_tokens":55946,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":176},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09d2d379-4cbc-4745-9b7a-9acf62397c86","uuid":"497e0bfa-5690-475a-8ece-d4572aae2f47","request_id":"req_011Cbxgbhs5rNmtS3nRbTnfH"},{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HDzTssRKFj3Rdco4aea37r","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/task-002-w3/tests/test_ui.py (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09d2d379-4cbc-4745-9b7a-9acf62397c86","uuid":"b135b682-4c90-46aa-8ce4-bd472fcbac1a","timestamp":"2026-06-12T03:50:19.685Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Volumes/990EVO4TB/Dev/wg4/task-002-w3/tests/test_ui.py","content":"import unittest\nfrom unittest.mock import patch\n\nfrom word_garden.game import GameState, MSG_CORRECT, MSG_INCORRECT\nfrom word_garden.main import GOODBYE_MESSAGE, main\nfrom word_garden.ui import (\n    LOSS_BODY,\n    LOSS_HEADER_ASCII,\n    LOSS_HEADER_EMOJI,\n    LOSS_WORD_PREFIX,\n    TITLE_ASCII,\n    TITLE_EMOJI,\n    WIN_BODY,\n    WIN_HEADER_ASCII,\n    WIN_HEADER_EMOJI,\n    WIN_WORD_PREFIX,\n    loss_screen,\n    render,\n    win_screen,\n)\n\n\ndef _make_state(**kwargs) -> GameState:\n    \"\"\"Build a GameState with sensible defaults, overridden by kwargs.\"\"\"\n    defaults = dict(\n        secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n        guessed_letters=set(),\n        remaining_water=6,\n        weed_count=0,\n        max_water=6,\n    )\n    defaults.update(kwargs)\n    return GameState(**defaults)\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# render — emoji mode\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nclass TestRenderEmojiMode(unittest.TestCase):\n    def test_contains_title(self):\n        state = _make_state()\n        output = render(state)\n        self.assertIn(TITLE_EMOJI, output)\n\n    def test_water_line_has_label_count_and_symbols(self):\n        state = _make_state(remaining_water=4, max_water=6)\n        output = render(state)\n        self.assertIn(\"Water:\", output)\n        self.assertIn(\"4/6\", output)\n        self.assertIn(\"💧💧💧💧\", output)\n\n    def test_weed_line_has_label_count_and_symbols(self):\n        state = _make_state(weed_count=2)\n        output = render(state)\n        self.assertIn(\"Weeds:\", output)\n        self.assertIn(\"2\", output)\n        self.assertIn(\"🌿🌿\", output)\n\n    def test_weed_line_shows_zero_when_no_weeds(self):\n        state = _make_state(weed_count=0)\n        output = render(state)\n        self.assertIn(\"Weeds:    0\", output)\n\n    def test_guessed_letters_sorted_space_separated(self):\n        state = _make_state(guessed_letters={\"E\", \"A\", \"R\"})\n        output = render(state)\n        self.assertIn(\"A E R\", output)\n\n    def test_masked_word_shown(self):\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"CAT\", guessed_letters={\"A\"})\n        output = render(state)\n        self.assertIn(\"_ A _\", output)\n\n    def test_status_message_included_when_present(self):\n        state = _make_state(status_message=MSG_CORRECT)\n        output = render(state)\n        self.assertIn(MSG_CORRECT, output)\n\n    def test_no_status_message_when_empty(self):\n        state = _make_state(status_message=\"\")\n        output = render(state)\n        self.assertNotIn(MSG_CORRECT, output)\n        self.assertNotIn(MSG_INCORRECT, output)\n\n    def test_output_order(self):\n        state = _make_state(\n            secret_word=\"CAT\",\n            guessed_letters={\"A\"},\n            remaining_water=4,\n            max_water=6,\n            weed_count=2,\n            status_message=MSG_CORRECT,\n        )\n        output = render(state)\n        title_pos = output.index(TITLE_EMOJI)\n        word_pos = output.index(\"Word:\")\n        guessed_pos = output.index(\"Guessed:\")\n        water_pos = output.index(\"Water:\")\n        weed_pos = output.index(\"Weeds:\")\n        msg_pos = output.index(MSG_CORRECT)\n        self.assertLess(title_pos, word_pos)\n        self.assertLess(word_pos, guessed_pos)\n        self.assertLess(guessed_pos, water_pos)\n        self.assertLess(water_pos, weed_pos)\n        self.assertLess(weed_pos, msg_pos)\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# render — ASCII mode\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nclass TestRenderAsciiMode(unittest.TestCase):\n    def test_title_is_ascii(self):\n        state = _make_state()\n        output = render(state, ascii_mode=True)\n        self.assertIn(TITLE_ASCII, output)\n        self.assertNotIn(TITLE_EMOJI, output)\n\n    def test_output_contains_no_non_ascii(self):\n        state = _make_state(\n            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n            guessed_letters={\"G\", \"A\"},\n            remaining_water=4,\n            max_water=6,\n            weed_count=2,\n            status_message=MSG_INCORRECT,\n        )\n        output = render(state, ascii_mode=True)\n        self.assertTrue(\n            output.isascii(),\n            f\"Non-ASCII characters found in ASCII render output:\\n{output!r}\",\n        )\n\n    def test_water_symbols_use_brackets(self):\n        state = _make_state(remaining_water=3, max_water=6)\n        output = render(state, ascii_mode=True)\n        self.assertIn(\"3/6 [***]\", output)\n\n    def test_weed_symbols_use_brackets(self):\n        state = _make_state(weed_count=2)\n        output = render(state, ascii_mode=True)\n        self.assertIn(\"2 [--]\", output)\n\n    def test_no_emoji_in_ascii_mode(self):\n        state = _make_state(weed_count=2, remaining_water=3)\n        output = render(state, ascii_mode=True)\n        self.assertNotIn(\"💧\", output)\n        self.assertNotIn(\"🌿\", output)\n        self.assertNotIn(\"🌱\", output)\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Growth stages\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nclass TestGrowthStages(unittest.TestCase):\n    def test_start_stage_when_no_letters_revealed(self):\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\", guessed_letters=set())\n        output = render(state, ascii_mode=True)\n        self.assertIn(\"[seed]\", output)\n\n    def test_progress_stage_when_some_letters_revealed(self):\n        # GARDEN has 6 unique letters; reveal 1 → 1/6 ≈ 17% (below 60%)\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\", guessed_letters={\"G\"})\n        output = render(state, ascii_mode=True)\n        self.assertIn(\"[plant]\", output)\n\n    def test_near_win_stage_when_most_letters_revealed(self):\n        # GARDEN: reveal 4 of 6 unique letters → 67% (above 60% threshold)\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\", guessed_letters={\"G\", \"A\", \"R\", \"D\"})\n        output = render(state, ascii_mode=True)\n        self.assertIn(\"[bud]\", output)\n\n    def test_win_stage_when_game_won(self):\n        state = _make_state(game_over=True, won=True)\n        output = render(state, ascii_mode=True)\n        self.assertIn(\"[flower]\", output)\n\n    def test_loss_stage_when_game_lost(self):\n        state = _make_state(game_over=True, won=False, remaining_water=0)\n        output = render(state, ascii_mode=True)\n        self.assertIn(\"[wilted]\", output)\n\n    def test_near_win_stage_exactly_at_threshold(self):\n        # \"AB\": 2 unique letters; reveal both → 100% > 60%\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"AB\", guessed_letters={\"A\", \"B\"})\n        # won would not be set on the state itself, just guessed_letters\n        # (we're testing the stage logic, not the full win flow)\n        output = render(state, ascii_mode=True)\n        self.assertIn(\"[bud]\", output)\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# win_screen and loss_screen\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nclass TestWinScreen(unittest.TestCase):\n    def test_emoji_mode_contains_header_and_word(self):\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\")\n        output = win_screen(state)\n        self.assertIn(WIN_HEADER_EMOJI, output)\n        self.assertIn(f\"{WIN_WORD_PREFIX}GARDEN\", output)\n        self.assertIn(WIN_BODY, output)\n\n    def test_ascii_mode_contains_header_and_word(self):\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\")\n        output = win_screen(state, ascii_mode=True)\n        self.assertIn(WIN_HEADER_ASCII, output)\n        self.assertIn(f\"{WIN_WORD_PREFIX}GARDEN\", output)\n        self.assertIn(WIN_BODY, output)\n\n    def test_ascii_mode_no_non_ascii_characters(self):\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\")\n        output = win_screen(state, ascii_mode=True)\n        self.assertTrue(output.isascii(), f\"Non-ASCII found in win_screen:\\n{output!r}\")\n\n    def test_emoji_mode_absent_in_ascii_win_screen(self):\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\")\n        output = win_screen(state, ascii_mode=True)\n        self.assertNotIn(WIN_HEADER_EMOJI, output)\n\n\nclass TestLossScreen(unittest.TestCase):\n    def test_emoji_mode_contains_header_and_word(self):\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\")\n        output = loss_screen(state)\n        self.assertIn(LOSS_HEADER_EMOJI, output)\n        self.assertIn(f\"{LOSS_WORD_PREFIX}GARDEN\", output)\n        self.assertIn(LOSS_BODY, output)\n\n    def test_ascii_mode_contains_header_and_word(self):\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\")\n        output = loss_screen(state, ascii_mode=True)\n        self.assertIn(LOSS_HEADER_ASCII, output)\n        self.assertIn(f\"{LOSS_WORD_PREFIX}GARDEN\", output)\n        self.assertIn(LOSS_BODY, output)\n\n    def test_ascii_mode_no_non_ascii_characters(self):\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"GARDEN\")\n        output = loss_screen(state, ascii_mode=True)\n        self.assertTrue(output.isascii(), f\"Non-ASCII found in loss_screen:\\n{output!r}\")\n\n    def test_loss_screen_reveals_secret_word(self):\n        state = _make_state(secret_word=\"PYTHON\")\n        output = loss_screen(state)\n        self.assertIn(\"PYTHON\", output)\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# End-to-end main() tests\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nclass TestMainEndToEnd(unittest.TestCase):\n    \"\"\"Scripted game runs using injected input/output functions.\"\"\"\n\n    def _run_main(self, initial_state, inputs, ascii_mode=False):\n        \"\"\"Run main() with a fixed initial state and scripted inputs.\"\"\"\n        outputs = []\n        input_iter = iter(inputs)\n\n        argv = [\"--ascii\"] if ascii_mode else []\n        with patch(\"word_garden.main.new_game\", return_value=initial_state):\n            exit_code = main(\n                argv=argv,\n                input_fn=lambda prompt=\"\": next(input_iter),\n                output_fn=outputs.append,\n            )\n\n        return exit_code, outputs\n\n    def test_win_scenario_shows_win_screen(self):\n        # \"CAT\": guess C, A, T → all letters revealed → win\n        initial = GameState(\n            secret_word=\"CAT\",\n            guessed_letters=set(),\n            remaining_water=6,\n            weed_count=0,\n            max_water=6,\n        )\n        exit_code, outputs = self._run_main(initial, [\"C\", \"A\", \"T\"], ascii_mode=True)\n\n        full_output = \"\\n\".join(outputs)\n        self.assertEqual(exit_code, 0)\n        self.assertIn(WIN_HEADER_ASCII, full_output)\n        self.assertIn(f\"{WIN_WORD_PREFIX}CAT\", full_output)\n        self.assertIn(WIN_BODY, full_output)\n\n    def test_loss_scenario_shows_loss_screen_with_word(self):\n        # \"GARDEN\" with 2 water: guess Z, X → both wrong → water runs out\n        initial = GameState(\n            secret_word=\"GARDEN\",\n            guessed_letters=set(),\n            remaining_water=2,\n            weed_count=0,\n            max_water=2,\n        )\n        exit_code, outputs = self._run_main(initial, [\"Z\", \"X\"], ascii_mode=True)\n\n        full_output = \"\\n\".join(outputs)\n        self.assertEqual(exit_code, 0)\n        self.assertIn(LOSS_HEADER_ASCII, full_output)\n        self.assertIn(f\"{LOSS_WORD_PREFIX}GARDEN\", full_output)\n        self.assertIn(LOSS_BODY, full_output)\n\n    def test_invalid_input_does_not_consume_turn(self):\n        # \"AB\": one wrong guess (Z) and one valid letter (B) — then A to win.\n        # If invalid input consumed a turn we would lose early.\n        initial = GameState(\n            secret_word=\"AB\",\n            guessed_letters=set(),\n            remaining_water=1,\n            weed_count=0,\n            max_water=1,\n        )\n        # \"7\" is invalid, \"A\" and \"B\" are valid wins\n        exit_code, outputs = self._run_main(initial, [\"7\", \"A\", \"B\"], ascii_mode=True)\n\n        full_output = \"\\n\".join(outputs)\n        self.assertEqual(exit_code, 0)\n        self.assertIn(WIN_HEADER_ASCII, full_output)\n\n    def test_eof_exits_cleanly(self):\n        initial = _make_state()\n        outputs = []\n\n        with patch(\"word_garden.main.new_game\", return_value=initial):\n            exit_code = main(\n                argv=[\"--ascii\"],\n                input_fn=lambda prompt=\"\": (_ for _ in ()).throw(EOFError()),\n                output_fn=outputs.append,\n            )\n\n        self.assertEqual(exit_code, 0)\n        self.assertIn(GOODBYE_MESSAGE, \"\\n\".join(outputs))\n\n    def test_keyboard_interrupt_exits_cleanly(self):\n        initial = _make_state()\n        outputs = []\n\n        with patch(\"word_garden.main.new_game\", return_value=initial):\n            exit_code = main(\n                argv=[\"--ascii\"],\n                input_fn=lambda prompt=\"\": (_ for _ in ()).throw(KeyboardInterrupt()),\n                output_fn=outputs.append,\n            )\n\n        self.assertEqual(exit_code, 0)\n        self.assertIn(GOODBYE_MESSAGE, \"\\n\".join(outputs))\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null,"userModified":false}},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01EqrNTghpuunSMg8587ksyJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me run the tests to see how they do:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4073,"cache_read_input_tokens":56122,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4073},"output_tokens":7,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09d2d379-4cbc-4745-9b7a-9acf62397c86","uuid":"0eaac479-4959-474c-92ff-86bfd594c838","request_id":"req_011CbxgfE76Eb2fgm7PW55Zc"},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01EqrNTghpuunSMg8587ksyJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu